On November 21, 2017, the President signed into law several bills. These include the "Federal Agency Mail Management Act of 2017," which requires the General Services Administration to provide guidance and assistance to Federal agencies in processing mail effectively. Another bill is the "VA Prescription Data Accountability Act of 2017," which mandates the Department of Veterans Affairs to disclose information about covered individuals to State controlled substance monitoring programs to prevent misuse and diversion of prescription medications. The "FEMA Accountability, Modernization and Transparency Act of 2017" requires the Federal Emergency Management Agency to include specific features in the modernization of grant systems for disaster assistance to improve accessibility and transparency for applicants. Additionally, the "FITARA Enhancement Act of 2017" extends and makes permanent certain provisions of the Federal Information Technology Acquisition Reform Act. Finally, the "Veterans Apprenticeship and Labor Opportunity Reform (VALOR) Act of 2017" designates State approving agencies for multi-state apprenticeship programs for the educational assistance programs of the Department of Veterans Affairs.